base class for error with custom model (GDEV-1021) (#6)

Added a base class that upon subclassing can be configured
with a custom data model and can be used to
generate custom body model.
These custom models are useful for instance when
constructing an openapi doc with FastAPI.

Bump version to 0.2.0.

improve custom model naming (GDEV-1023) (#7)

Previously, the custom body model class was renamed by
changing the __name__ attribute. However, that implementation
let to problems with openapi-generation by FastAPI.

Now renaming of classes is realized by subclassing via the type()
builtin.

Bump version to 0.2.1

renamed exceptionId to exception_id

to avoid naming mistakes between python and OpenAPI.

fix titles in FastAPI_generated OpenAPI (GDEV-1406) (#11)

When custom exceptions based on HttpCustomExceptionBase where used
together with FastAPI to generate an OpenAPI documentation,
the titles were wrong.

The titles were attempted to be set explicitly in the base class.
That worked fine for the pydantic-based schema validation, however caused problems wit
the OpenAPI generator of FastAPI,
which automatically sets the title based
on the class name.
Simply removing the explicit title definition thus resolved the problem.

Bumps version to 0.2.4.
